  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-4 pb-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/strategy/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Strategy</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Parallel Plays</span>
      </nav>

      <BlogCrossLinks title="Creating Parallel Plays — Score Multiple Words in One Turn" />

      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4 mt-2">Creating Parallel Plays</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Score multiple words in a single turn — the most powerful technique in competitive Scrabble</p>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-07-15">July 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Most Scrabble players think in one direction — place a word across or down. But the highest-scoring players think in two dimensions simultaneously. A parallel play lets you score your main word <em>plus</em> every two-letter cross-word formed alongside an existing word. One move, multiple scores. It's the single most effective scoring technique in competitive Scrabble.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Is a Parallel Play?</h2>

      <p>A parallel play means placing your word directly beside an existing word — either above, below, or next to it — so that every touching pair of letters forms a valid two-letter word. You score points for ALL the new words created.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Concept</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">When you play a word parallel to an existing word, you score: <span class="text-white font-medium">your main word + every 2-letter cross-word formed</span>. A 4-letter parallel play can create 5 words scored simultaneously.</p>
      </div>

      <p>For example, if RATE is on the board and you place ONES directly below it:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/40 font-mono text-center">
        <p class="text-lg text-white tracking-[0.3em] mb-1">R A T E</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-green-400 tracking-[0.3em]">O N E S</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-3">Cross-words formed: RO, AN, TE, ES — plus ONES itself = 5 words scored!</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Parallel Plays Are So Powerful</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">40-60+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points per play</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2-5×</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Score multiplier</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">127</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid 2-letter words</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>A normal word might score 15-20 points on its own. But played parallel to an existing word, the same tiles can score 40-60+ because each adjacent letter pair adds to your total. Premium squares multiply the effect even further — a letter on a Double Letter Score counts for BOTH the main word and the cross-word.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Normal Play</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ONES across an open lane = 4 pts</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Parallel Play</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ONES parallel to RATE = 4 + RO(2) + AN(2) + TE(2) + ES(2) = 12+ pts</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Two-Letter Words You Must Know</h2>

      <p>Parallel plays live and die by your knowledge of valid two-letter words. Every adjacent pair must be valid, or the entire play is illegal. There are 127 valid two-letter words in SOWPODS — memorising them unlocks the entire parallel play strategy.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XU</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">2 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">2 pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/best-two-letter-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
