      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How to Spot Parallel Opportunities</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Step-by-Step Process</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Scan the board edges</strong> — look for words with open space directly above or below them</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Check each letter pair</strong> — for every position, ask "does MY letter + THEIR letter form a valid 2-letter word?"</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Verify ALL positions</strong> — every adjacent pair must be valid, not just most of them</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-white">Calculate the total</strong> — add up your main word + all cross-words to see if it beats your best alternative</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Common Parallel Play Patterns</h2>

      <p>Experienced players recognize recurring letter combinations that work in parallel. Here are the most reliable patterns:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">S-hooking parallel:</span> Adding S to an existing word while playing your word alongside. The S forms the end of one word and extends another — double value from a single tile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Vowel-consonant alternation:</span> Words like AREA, OLEO, ALOE pair beautifully below consonant-heavy words because most vowel+consonant combos are valid 2-letter words.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">High-value tile dump:</span> Place Q, X, Z, or J in a parallel position where it forms QI, XI, ZA, or JO. You dump the difficult tile AND score it in two words simultaneously.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square exploitation:</span> A letter on DLS/TLS counts in BOTH the main word and cross-word. Place your highest-value tile on the premium square in the parallel position for maximum effect.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Use Parallel Plays</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Ideal Situations</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Board is tight with few open lanes. You have tiles that form valid 2-letter combos. Premium squares are accessible only from parallel positions. You need to dump Q/X/Z/J while scoring.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Avoid When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Board is wide open with better scoring lanes. You have a bingo (50-point bonus beats most parallels). Your parallel opens a TWS for your opponent. You're unsure about a 2-letter word's validity.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Practice Drill: Build Your Parallel Vision</h2>

      <p>Train your brain to see parallel opportunities automatically:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Daily Exercise</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Pick any word on the board. For each letter, write down all valid 2-letter words that START or END with that letter. Now try to form a word using those constraints. Do this for 5 words per game and within a week, you'll spot parallels naturally.</p>
      </div>

